name: the law of the jungle is like this
description:
I took this picture in 2017 in the middle of an incredible day with some friends who came to visit me here in Rio, we woke up early that day to do graffiti in some specific places, with a long mission and with enough material to paint some more on the street, we found this place apparently mind abandoned but it was not, we arrived and soon we met the people responsible for the space and that authorized us to do our arts throughout the building, inside we had a view of how the law of the streets of Rio de Janeiro works, In the middle of a cold place, without windows, clean but with a certain accumulation of garbage in some corners, there were about 50 people living in this place and there were some strict rules, one of them was not to take what was not given, a rule broken by one of the women who lived there that was summoned to court, with the lost cause and the judge giving the verdict the woman was in the middle of a circle formed only by women and was beaten for two minutes with the only right to defend herself, This photo they asked me to take as a sign that everything was calm.
